{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-9a15d618073297c3", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# CosyVoice 3: Towards In-the-wild Speech Generation via Scaling-up and Post-training\narXiv: 2505.17589\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Changfeng Gao, Yuxuan Wang, Fan Yu, Tianyu Zhao, Hao Wang, Xiang Lv, Hui Wang, Chongjia Ni, Xian Shi, Keyu An, Guanrou Yang, Yabin Li, Yanni Chen, Zhifu Gao, Qian Chen, Yue Gu, Mengzhe Chen, Yafeng Chen, Shiliang Zhang, Wen Wang, Jieping Ye\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a novel speech tokenizer derived from a large audio understanding model via supervised multi-task training to better capture paralinguistic information.\n  2. We introduce a differentiable reward optimization (DiffRO) method for post-training that directly optimizes speech tokens using back-propagation.\n  3. We validate dataset size scaling by expanding training data from ten thousand to one million hours, covering 9 languages and 18 Chinese dialects.\n  4. We demonstrate model size scaling by increasing parameters from 0.5 billion to 1.5 billion, which enhances prosody naturalness and performance on difficult tasks.\n  5. We release the CV3-Eval benchmark for zero-shot speech synthesis in the wild, featuring authentic in-the-wild data across diverse languages, domains, and emotions.\n\nTags: TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/控制-指令合成, TTS/功能-RL优化, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-方言小语种, TTS/功能-多说话人, 压缩/监督-有监督, 压缩/语义声学-混合\n---\n# VoxCPM2 Technical Report\narXiv: 2606.06928\nAuthors: Yixuan Zhou, Guoyang Zeng, Xin Liu, Xiang Li, Renjie Yu, Jiancheng Gui, Jiaheng Wu, Ziyang Wang, Xudong Shen, Runchuan Ye, Zhisheng Zhang, Jiuyang Zhou, Bingsong Bai, Weiyue Sun, Mengyuan Deng, Qundong Shi, Zhiyong Wu, Zhiyuan Liu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n---captalk---\n# CapTalk: Unified Voice Design for Single-Utterance and Dialogue Speech Generation\narXiv: 2604.08363\nAuthors: Xiaosu Su, Zihan Sun, Peilei Jia, Jun Gao\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose CapTalk, a unified caption-conditioned text-audio autoregressive framework that supports both single-utterance and dialogue voice design using utterance-level and speaker-level captions, alongside a CoT control sequence for turn-level expressive control.\n  2. We introduce a hierarchical variational conditioning mechanism with an utterance-level speaker encoder to balance stable timbre preservation and context-adaptive expression, enabling designed timbre reuse while keeping expression aligned with the current utterance and dialogue context.\n  3. We build a comprehensive evaluation protocol for both single-utterance and dialogue settings, including human evaluation for single-utterance speech and dialogue-oriented CoT prediction, controllability, and comparative evaluation.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/控制-NL描述, TTS/控制-风格标签, TTS/功能-多说话人", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "01228239-e95d-406a-8754-e0196b731841", "uuid": "85b7bb96-42d2-4ec1-8b35-62f65188ac35", "timestamp": "2026-07-21T05:50:21.957Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# CosyVoice 3: Towards In-the-wild Speech Generation via Scaling-up and Post-training\narXiv: 2505.17589\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Changfeng Gao, Yuxuan Wang, Fan Yu, Tianyu Zhao, Hao Wang, Xiang Lv, Hui Wang, Chongjia Ni, Xian Shi, Keyu An, Guanrou Yang, Yabin Li, Yanni Chen, Zhifu Gao, Qian Chen, Yue Gu, Mengzhe Chen, Yafeng Chen, Shiliang Zhang, Wen Wang, Jieping Ye\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a novel speech tokenizer derived from a large audio understanding model via supervised multi-task training to better capture paralinguistic information.\n  2. We introduce a differentiable reward optimization (DiffRO) method for post-training that directly optimizes speech tokens using back-propagation.\n  3. We validate dataset size scaling by expanding training data from ten thousand to one million hours, covering 9 languages and 18 Chinese dialects.\n  4. We demonstrate model size scaling by increasing parameters from 0.5 billion to 1.5 billion, which enhances prosody naturalness and performance on difficult tasks.\n  5. We release the CV3-Eval benchmark for zero-shot speech synthesis in the wild, featuring authentic in-the-wild data across diverse languages, domains, and emotions.\n\nTags: TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/控制-指令合成, TTS/功能-RL优化, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-方言小语种, TTS/功能-多说话人, 压缩/监督-有监督, 压缩/语义声学-混合\n---\n# VoxCPM2 Technical Report\narXiv: 2606.06928\nAuthors: Yixuan Zhou, Guoyang Zeng, Xin Liu, Xiang Li, Renjie Yu, Jiancheng Gui, Jiaheng Wu, Ziyang Wang, Xudong Shen, Runchuan Ye, Zhisheng Zhang, Jiuyang Zhou, Bingsong Bai, Weiyue Sun, Mengyuan Deng, Qundong Shi, Zhiyong Wu, Zhiyuan Liu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n---captalk---\n# CapTalk: Unified Voice Design for Single-Utterance and Dialogue Speech Generation\narXiv: 2604.08363\nAuthors: Xiaosu Su, Zihan Sun, Peilei Jia, Jun Gao\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose CapTalk, a unified caption-conditioned text-audio autoregressive framework that supports both single-utterance and dialogue voice design using utterance-level and speaker-level captions, alongside a CoT control sequence for turn-level expressive control.\n  2. We introduce a hierarchical variational conditioning mechanism with an utterance-level speaker encoder to balance stable timbre preservation and context-adaptive expression, enabling designed timbre reuse while keeping expression aligned with the current utterance and dialogue context.\n  3. We build a comprehensive evaluation protocol for both single-utterance and dialogue settings, including human evaluation for single-utterance speech and dialogue-oriented CoT prediction, controllability, and comparative evaluation.\n\nTags: TT